    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/3504: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-31T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 31, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1250. Embassy’s telegram No. 1243, December 30, 7 p.m.<note n="51"
                        xml:id="d417fn51">Not printed.</note> The Foreign Office has issued a
                    statement containing the text of the exchange of notes<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d417fn52">Dated December 30, 1942, <hi rend="italic">Memoria de la
                            Secretariat de Relaciones Exteriores</hi>, 1942–1943 (Mexico, D. F.,
                        1943), pp. 457–460.</note> between Padilla<note n="53" xml:id="d417fn53">E.
                        Padilla, Mexican Foreign Minister.</note> and Sikorski<note n="54"
                        xml:id="d417fn54">Gen. Wladyslaw Sikorski, Polish Prime Minister.</note>
                    regarding a limited arrangement for the admission of Polish refugees to Mexico.
                    The number of Poles accepted will be in accordance with the capacity of the
                    country.</p>
                <p>Transportation to Mexico will be without expense to the Mexican Government.
                    Expenses of their sojourn will be borne by the Polish Government. Repatriation
                    at the expense of the Polish Government will take place at the first propitious
                    moment after the [war]. Poles while in Mexico will be distributed where they can
                    contribute to the economy of Mexico without [conflicting] with Mexican
                    citizens.</p>
                <p>Texts of the notes will be forwarded by airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
